title:Blueberry Scones
ingredients:4 cups flour//
3 tablespoons sugar//
4 teaspoons baking powder//
1/2 teaspoon bream of tarter//
1/2 teaspoon salt//
3/4 cup butter//
1 large egg//
1 1/2 cups half and half//
1 1/2 cups blueberries
instructions:Heat oven to 425F.//
Grease large baking sheet.//
In large bowl, combine flour, 2 tablespoons sugar, baking powder, salt, and cream of tartar.//
Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.//
Separate egg, and beat yolk with a fork.//
Stir in half and half.//
Add mixture to dry mixture and mix lightly with form to form a soft dough.//
Turn dough out onto lightly floured surface and knead 5-6 times.//
Gently knead in blueberries.//
Divide dough in half, rolling each into 7 inch rounds.//
Cut into 4 wedges each.//
Place scones 1 inch apart, on greased baking sheet.//
Pierce tops with a fork and brush with reserved egg white.//
Sprinkle with remaining 1 tablespoon sugar.//
Bake for 15-18 minutes.